    {"repo": "llvm/llvm-project", "path": "llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h", "symbol": "MachineFunction"}
  ],
  "text": "The LLVM code generation pipeline consists of five core stages: (1) SelectionDAGISel (llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/SelectionDAGISel.h) is the base class for instruction selection, implementing pattern matching that converts LLVM IR to target-specific SelectionDAG nodes. (2) SelectionDAGBuilder (llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/SelectionDAGBuilder.h) translates LLVM IR instructions into DAG nodes before instruction selection. (3) ScheduleDAGRRList (llvm/lib/CodeGen/SelectionDAG/ScheduleDAGRRList.cpp) implements instruction scheduling using register pressure reduction algorithms to optimize the order of machine operations. (4) RAGreedy (llvm/lib/CodeGen/RegAllocGreedy.h) is the greedy register allocator that assigns virtual registers to physical registers. (5) MachineFunction (llvm/include/llvm/CodeGen/MachineFunction.h) is the core data structure representing a function at the machine code level, containing machine basic blocks and machine instructions. Together, these components form the critical path from high-level IR through instruction selection, scheduling, and register allocation to produce optimized machine code."
}

